 one of the following browsers you can upgrade your existing browser by clicking one of the links below you will need to restart your computer in order to complete the upgrade download internet explorer download firefox download chrome download safari we strongly recommend that you upgrade now if you do not upgrade your browser you may experience functional or display issues on the pages you are attempting to access  upon clicking this link you will leave the first citizens bank website and go to a third party site third party sites may have a privacy policy different from first citizens bank and may provide less security than this site first citizens bank and its affiliates are not responsible for the products services and content on any third party website bob advantage friday     customer id user id enter  indicates a required field to sign in to bob advantage enter your customer id and user id and click the enter button to continue bob advantage secure sign in please wait first citizens bank is dedicated to maintaining the highest level of online security thats why weve made a commitment to protecting your financial information with some of the top internet security technology in the industry however your information may still be at risk if your personal or professional computer is compromised by a virus or malware to learn more about how to help protect your computer from malicious online software click here what we do our online banking system is designed to protect your information and privacy here are some of the security measures we have in place strong encryption information exchanged between your computer and our web server is secured through encryption encryption converts the information into a form that is unreadable as it travels along the internet you must have a browser that supports strong encryption to access the system in technical terms the browser must support bit encryption password protection to protect your password our system will periodically request that you change your password when changing your password you will be shown whether your password is considered weak medium or strong strong passwords are harder for a fraudster to guess please do not reveal your password to anyone and please commit your password to memory rather than writing it down where others may find it automatic logout you should always log out of the online banking facility when you are done if you forget our system will automatically log you out after a period of time protecting your privacy in order to protect your personal information you may be asked to enter security credentials before gaining access to pages that contain your address phone number and login credentials providing these credentials will confirm your identity so that only you can see and modify your personal information fraud protection in order to protect you against fraudulent transactions you may be asked to enter security credentials for any transaction that moves funds out of the bank for example a transfer to an external account or a bill payment what you can do first citizens is dedicated to maintaining the highest possible level of online security we consider it a great responsibility to protect the financial information you have entrusted to us however your financial information may still be at risk if your personal or professional computer is compromised by a virus or malicious software known as malware malware can be placed on your computer in multiple ways including clicking a link on a fake email made to look like it comes from a trusted company – often a bank everyone has an important role to play when it comes to information security and protecting confidential data we’ve sent you this message to remind you of some steps you can take to shield your computer from malware we recommend that you seek professional computer assistance to enable the following precautions use the internet cautiously internet activity including email can be intercepted and viewed by others phishing is an attempt by internet fraudsters to lure you into giving confidential information allowing them to gain access to your financial information use caution with email attachments and web links they could contain malware never open email attachments or click links from people you dont know  just delete them be careful opening email attachments or clicking on links from people you do know their computer may have been compromised and they may be unknowingly participating in the spread of malware be aware of email fraud senders of emails may have crafted the emails in such a way that they appear to be from someone known to the business a common occurrence is to make the email look like it was sent by the cfo or even the ceo of the business given this possibility the “from” address should not be trusted recently fraudsters posing as vendors clients or employees have begun sending businesses emails requesting wire transfers the business initiates a wire based on instructions in the email only to learn that their vendor client or employees email account had been compromised and the wire request was fraudulent fraudsters have also convinced businesses to update payment information for legitimate vendors please note that sending a wire or initiating any transaction based solely on an email request can be very risky we encourage you to verify such requests by contacting your vendors clients and employees using an alternative method such as a phone call to a known valid number for more information please review the fbi alert at httpwwwicgovmediaaspx notify first citizens if you receive a request to provide confidential data if you are using business online banking advantage® and encounter different functionality wording pictures or text than what you are used to – or if you are being prompted for information that you do not normally have to provide – contact us immediately this may be an indication that your computer has been infected by malware if you have concerns that your computer is compromised in any way stop using it for sensitive transactions until you can have it safely cleaned use antivirus and firewall products on all computers we suggest that you install antivirus products on your computer and enable the firewall features on your computer and network equipment there are several reliable commercial products available at low or no cost regularly install operating system and software updates it is extremely important that you make sure your computer has all of the most current security updates set your computer to automatically update your operating system via microsoft update windows update or apple software update as well as your addins such as adobe flash and adobe reader with all of the latest security patches each product generally has an option to “check for updates” automatically do not use operating systems or other software that are no longer supported security of such products is no longer being maintained continued use puts you at risk of compromise this includes windows xp and old browsers such as ie  and older regularly back up data on your computer backing up data regularly ensures that sensitive documents and files are safe secure and recoverable in the event of a hardware failure or malware intrusion for optimal protection we recommend rotating multiple backups with at least one backup to a disconnected storage medium and an offsite location at all times take note of any strange or unusual behavior if you notice that your computer is running slower than usual or if you start seeing strange behavior such as unexpected popup windows or requests for never before requested information at login or transaction time this may be an indication of a potential problem contact your computer support professional to diagnose and remove any malware establish a dedicated computer for sensitive transactions if possible dedicate a single computer for use by everyone in your home or office for conducting sensitive transactions such as online banking issuing wires or making ach payments if a workstation computer is used for online banking we recommend that it not be used for general web browsing or social networking use bob advantage chk from a separate device for maximum security we recommend that the chk application be installed on a either an iphone or android smart phone or on a separate pc desktop from that used to login to bob advantage monitor and reconcile your accounts daily to make sure your accounts have not been compromised reconcile your financial transactions on a regular basis if anything looks incorrect or out of the ordinary contact first citizens immediately using the phone numbers listed below do not access your bank accounts at internet cafes or from public wifi hotspots public internet connections that you find in airports coffee shops and internet cafes usually do not have the level of security necessary to protect your sensitive financial information rebuild your computer if it becomes infected although you may have run several antivirus scans against your computer industry experts recommend that a complete rebuild of the computer is the only sure way to remove the threat completely we realize that this is not a convenient solution however we appreciate how sensitive your data and finances are and want you to be aware of every possible precaution you can take to protect your private information please call fcbbiz  monday  saturday  am   pm et if you have any questions or concerns first citizens takes online security very seriously thank you for taking the time to learn more about how to protect your computer from these harmful threats member fdic the information contained in this website regarding antivirus software is for general information purposes only we make no representations or warranties of any kind about the reliability suitability or availability of the products the inclusion of any links does not necessarily imply a recommendation or endorsement of any product   first citizens bank business banking  first citizens bank javascript is required for this site to function properly find instructions for how to enable javascript here atms  locations about first citizens careers contact us send message request call customer support call us fc direct personal business wealth a framework to manage your business finances business banking business checkingoptions to manage your business finances from simple accounts to comprehensive packagescompare accountsread the business checking faqsfind out what you need to get startedbusiness savingsaccounts that keep your business finances safe including traditional savings money market accounts and cdscompare accountsread the business savings faqshow much do you need to start a businessvisa® businessdebit cardan easy and safe way to pay for business services and supplieslearn morelearn about chip card securitylearn about visa® checkoutbob advantage®access accounts pay bills make transfers and morelearn moreview the bob advantage® demoread the bob advantage® faqsmerchant card processinggive customers more payment options and streamline operationslearn moreproject your cash flowprotect your business with fraud prevention servicesfirst citizens rewards® business visa® carddesigned for businesses who want to earn rewards with no annual feelearn moreread the business credit card faqslearn how to accelerate your reward earningsyou may also be interested in your venture first® business account requirements financial ratio analysis how to finance your business remote image deposit online payroll services  view legal disclosures− hide legal disclosuresaccount openings and credit are subject to bank approval upon clicking this link you will leave the first citizens bank website and go to a third party site third party sites may have a privacy policy different from first citizens bank and may provide less security than this site first citizens bank and its affiliates are not