 products and services and investments and retirement including individual retirement accounts and retirement planning the company’s business products and services include banking  firstcitizens bank  trust company a statechartered commercial bank provides banking services to individuals businesses professionals and the medical community it offers personal banking services including checking accounts savings accounts and cds debit cards and online and mobile banking loans and credit services such as credit cards home equity loans and lines of credit mortgage loans refinancing auto loans and other personal loans and lines of credit online and mobile services insurance products and services and investments and retirement including individual retirement accounts and retirement planning the company’s business products and services include banking payment acceptance equipment finance and leasing insurance and online payroll business checking accounts business online banking business debit cards business credit cards merchant services and business savings accounts and cds credit and financing services such as equipment financing and leasing business lines of credit and business loans cash management services including merchant card processing payroll solutions remote image deposits manage payables manage receivables liquidity management reconciliation and reporting and fraud prevention and insurance products and services firstcitizens bank  trust company was formerly known as bank of smithfield and changed its name to firstcitizens bank  trust company in  the company was founded in  and is based in raleigh north carolina it has branches in arizona california colorado district of columbia florida georgia kansas maryland missouri new mexico north carolina oklahoma oregon south carolina tennessee texas virginia washington and west virginia firstcitizens bank  trust company operates as a subsidiary of first citizens bancshares inc detailed description  fayetteville streetwake countyraleigh nc united statesfounded in  phone  fax  wwwfirstcitizenscom key executives for firstcitizens bank  trust company mr frank b holding jr chairman and chief executive officer age  mr peter m bristow jr president and director age  mr craig l nix chief financial officer age  mr edward lee willingham iv chief operating officer age  mrs lorie k rupp chief accounting officer and senior vice president age  compensation as of fiscal year  firstcitizens bank  trust company key developments randy martin joins first citizens bank as director of private banking jul   randy martin has joined first citizens bank as director of private banking in this role martin is responsible for building growing and managing the company’s private banking business which provides clients with structured custompackaged credit and banking deposit services and access to products that help manage changing interest rates with  years of financial services industry experience martin joins first citizens from capital one bank in mclean va where he headed up private banking national underwriting and commercial credit services martin currently serves as a member of the panel and the chairman’s committee for the risk management association rma north american private lending roundtable the us department of housing and urban development announces agreement with firstcitizens bank and trust company to resolve fair lending complaint jun   the us department of housing and urban development announced an agreement with firstcitizens bank and trust company resolving allegations that the bank denied mortgage loans to african american latino and asian american mortgage applicants at a disproportionately higher rate than white applicants huds investigation concerned retail loans originated by the banks predecessor first citizens bank and trust co in  and  hud filed a complaint against first citizens bank and trust co in  after conducting an analysis of  home mortgage disclosure act hmda data in january  the south carolinabased bank was merged into firstcitizens bank and trust company a north carolinachartered commercial lender as the successor firstcitizens bank and trust company continued to cooperate with hud throughout this investigation and ultimate resolution announced as part of the settlement firstcitizens agreed to take several steps to ensure and protect equal access to credit including refraining from unlawful consideration of race or national origin when selecting sites for branch offices and services offered conducting marketing and defining community reinvestment act assessment areas in addition firstcitizens will make  available to nonprofit organizations that provide credit and housing counseling financial literacy training and related programs to firsttime homebuyers in south carolina adopt a new standardized and objective set of guidelines for a second review of retail channel residential loan applications initially denied by the automated underwriting system require all of its employees and agents who have substantial involvement in manual underwriting of mortgages in their retail channel to attend fair housing training hire three mortgage banker market specialists that will focus on diverse lending in the charlestonnorth charlestonsummerville columbia and greenvilleandersonmauldin metro areas first citizens bank appoints chris riley as commercial banking manager for columbia upstate sc may   chris riley has returned to first citizens bank as manager of commercial banking for the columbia and greenvillespartanburg areas he leads first citizens commercial banking teams for these markets focusing on developing and managing relationships with local companies riley rejoins first citizens from regions financial corporation where he most recently served as south carolina market president for the past six years prior to this he was market president at the former wachovia corporation in greenville sc but started the first  years of his banking career with 